# Property Details API Tests
# Use with REST Client extension in VS Code or any HTTP client

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@userToken = YOUR_USER_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
@adminToken = YOUR_ADMIN_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### 1. Register User (if needed)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "testuser@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "firstName": "Test",
  "lastName": "User",
  "phone": "1234567890"
}

### 2. Login User
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "testuser@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Create Property WITH all new fields
POST {{baseUrl}}/properties
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Modern Downtown Apartment",
  "description": "Spacious 2-bedroom apartment in the heart of downtown with stunning city views",
  "price": 350000,
  "location": "123 Main St, Apt 5B, New York, NY 10001",
  "latitude": 40.7489,
  "longitude": -73.9680,
  "area": 85.5,
  "rooms": 2,
  "floor": 5
}

### 4. Create Property WITHOUT new fields (backward compatible)
POST {{baseUrl}}/properties
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Classic Family Home",
  "description": "Beautiful 4-bedroom house in quiet neighborhood",
  "price": 450000,
  "location": "456 Oak Avenue, Boston, MA 02101"
}

### 5. Create Property with PARTIAL new fields
POST {{baseUrl}}/properties
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Cozy Studio",
  "description": "Perfect for students or young professionals",
  "price": 150000,
  "location": "789 Elm Street, Brooklyn, NY 11201",
  "rooms": 1,
  "floor": 2
}

### 6. Get All Properties (check if new fields appear)
GET {{baseUrl}}/properties
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

### 7. Get Single Property with Details
GET {{baseUrl}}/properties/1
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

### 8. Update Property - Only new fields
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/properties/1
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "area": 90,
  "rooms": 3
}

### 9. Update Property - Mix of old and new fields
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/properties/1
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "price": 360000,
  "latitude": 40.7500,
  "longitude": -73.9700,
  "floor": 6
}

### 10. Create Property - Test Validation (should fail - negative rooms)
POST {{baseUrl}}/properties
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Test Validation",
  "description": "This should fail",
  "price": 100000,
  "location": "Test Location",
  "rooms": -1
}

### 11. Create Property - Test Validation (should fail - negative area)
POST {{baseUrl}}/properties
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Test Validation",
  "description": "This should fail",
  "price": 100000,
  "location": "Test Location",
  "area": -50
}

### 12. Create Property - Basement floor (negative floor is allowed)
POST {{baseUrl}}/properties
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Basement Office Space",
  "description": "Commercial space in basement level",
  "price": 200000,
  "location": "100 Business Plaza, Chicago, IL 60601",
  "latitude": 41.8781,
  "longitude": -87.6298,
  "area": 120,
  "rooms": 3,
  "floor": -1
}

### 13. Create Property with Coordinates (for Google Maps testing)
POST {{baseUrl}}/properties
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Beachfront Condo",
  "description": "Luxury condo with ocean views",
  "price": 750000,
  "location": "2000 Ocean Drive, Miami Beach, FL 33139",
  "latitude": 25.7907,
  "longitude": -80.1300,
  "area": 150,
  "rooms": 3,
  "floor": 10
}

### Google Maps Link Format (use the coordinates above)
# https://www.google.com/maps?q=25.7907,-80.1300

### 14. Get Property and Check Response Format
GET {{baseUrl}}/properties/1
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

# Expected Response:
# {
#   "id": 1,
#   "title": "...",
#   "description": "...",
#   "price": 350000,
#   "location": "123 Main St...",
#   "latitude": 40.7489,
#   "longitude": -73.9680,
#   "area": 85.5,
#   "rooms": 2,
#   "floor": 5,
#   "status": "ACTIVE",
#   "ownerId": 2,
#   "owner": { ... },
#   "createdAt": "...",
#   "updatedAt": "...",
#   "images": []
# }
